@NODE Introduction "Introduction"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Introduction@{ub}



Screen Mug Shot is a simply Commodity that will save an image of either
the active window or screen to an IFF file.


@ENDNODE


@NODE UsingProgram "Using Screen Mug Shot"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Using Screen Mug Shot@{ub}



@{"  " LINK StartingProg} Starting Screen Mug Shot


@{"  " LINK MenuStrip} Menu Strip


@{"  " LINK MainEditor} Main Editor


@ENDNODE


@NODE StartingProg "Starting Screen Mug Shot"
@TOC UsingProgram
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Starting Screen Mug Shot@{ub}



This program may be started from the Workbench or the Shell window.


This program will detach from the Shell so you need not use Run or any other
variant.  There are a few command line arguments you may use when loading:



@{b}CX_POPUP/K@{ub}

Open the interface or not at startup.

Default: NO

ex: CX_POPUP=YES


@{b}CX_POPKEY/K@{ub}

Key sequence to open the user interface.

Default: alt numericpad )

ex: CX_POPKEY "alt p"


@{b}CX_GRABWINDOW/K@{ub}

Key sequence to grab the active window.

Default: alt numericpad (

ex: CX_GRABWINDOW "alt w"


@{b}CX_GRABSCREEN/K@{ub}

Key sequence to grab the active screen.

Default: alt numericpad *

ex: CX_GRABSCREEN "alt s"


@{b}DELAY/K@{ub}

Number of seconds to wait before grabbing.  This will allow you to pull

down any menus, etc.

If set to 0, then no delay.

ex: DELAY 5


@{b}SAVEPATH/K@{ub}

Where to save the grabs.

ex: SAVEPATH=Work:Pics/


@{b}USEREQUESTER/K@{ub}

Will open a file requester to allowing custom naming of grab.

ex: USERQUESTER=TRUE


@{b}PUBSCREEN/K@{ub}

Name of public screen to open the interface on.


@{b}LANGUAGE/K@{ub}

Preferred locale strings language.

Language must be all lower case.



The arguments are not case sensitive and may be mixed in any order.

ex: ScreenMugShot CX_GRABWINDOW "alt w" DELAY 5


Only one copy may be run at one time.  You will be notified if more than
one copy is attempted to be executed.


@ENDNODE


@NODE MenuStrip "Menu Strip"
@TOC UsingProgram
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Menu Strip@{ub}



@{b}Load Preferences@{ub}

This will load the previously saved settings.


@{b}Save Preferences@{ub}

This will save the current settings.


@{b}About...@{ub}

Will open a large requester with some pertinent information about the program.


@{b}Quit@{ub}

Will terminate the program.


@ENDNODE


@NODE MainEditor "Main Editor"
@TOC UsingProgram
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Main Editor@{ub}



@{b}Pop Key@{ub}

Key sequence to open the user interface.


@{b}Grab Window@{ub}

Key sequence to grab the active window.


@{b}Grab Screen@{ub}

Key sequence to grab the active screen.


@{b}Delay@{ub}

Number of seconds to wait before grabbing.  This will allow time to pull down
a menu, etc.


@{b}Save Path@{ub}

Path to save grabs.


@{b}Use Requester@{ub}

If checked, will allow for custom naming of grabs.


@{b}Hide@{ub}

Close the user interface.


@{b}Quit@{ub}

This will terminate the program.


@ENDNODE


@NODE GadTools "GadTools"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}GadTools@{ub}



Thanks to Olaf `Olsen' Barthel, author of gtlayout.library.  It is by far
the best user interface package.  Also thanks for all his programming help.


The user interface is totally font and screen mode sensitive.  All
gadgets and the window will automatically adjust to match your preferences.


The latest features are utilized to get the most from the operating
system and to make the program the best of it's kind.


@ENDNODE


@NODE LocaleSupport "Locale Support"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Locale Support@{ub}



This is program is totally localized to allow support for foreign
languages.  A catalog may not be available for your language at this time,
but one will hopefully be available soon.


If you are willing to translate the strings to another language, please let
me know.  If you do offer, a perfect translation of all strings will be
expected.  It is all or nothing.  I will also be seeking your assistance for
future versions that have new strings.


@ENDNODE


